<headline>Beach Hazards Statement issued May 04 at 9:22PM CDT until May 05 at 9:00PM CDT by NWS Houston - Galveston</headline>
<description>...BEACH HAZARDS STATEMENT IN EFFECT THROUGH THURSDAY EVENING...
* WHAT...Persistent onshore winds maintaining a high risk of rip
currents and elevated surf along with elevated water levels to
area beaches.
* WHERE...Matagorda Islands, Brazoria Islands, Galveston Island
and Bolivar Peninsula Counties.
* WHEN...Through Thursday evening.
* IMPACTS...Rip currents can sweep even the best swimmers away
from shore into deeper water. Minor coastal flooding may be
possible from higher than usual water levels at high tide.</description>
<instruction>Remain out of the water to avoid hazardous swimming conditions.</instruction>
